The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Kale verdict on Wednesday
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: The three-member disciplinary committee probing the bribery allegations against Maharashtras Abhijit Kale, will meet in the city on Wednesday to announce its verdict. All members of the committee, BCCI president Jagmohan Dalmiya and vice-presidents Kamal Morarka and Ranbir Singh Mahendra will be present. Meanwhile, the BCCI will hold its third spin conclave in the city on Saturday. A working group, comprising NCA chairman Sunil Gavaskar and director Brijesh Patel, Bishan Singh Bedi, Erapalli Prasanna, V.V. Kumar, Ravi Shastri and Anil Kumble will meet to chalk out a detailed action plan for the spin wing. Srinivas Venkatraghavan will not be able to attend the meeting.  Copyright 
